column8: All these were only so many preparatory and alarming signs of the great catastrophe of Rome , when the country of the Scipios and C??sars should be consumed by a flame from Heaven , and the city of the seven hills , with her palaces , her temples , and her triumphal arches , should be buried in a vast lake of fire and brimstone .
